txt.en: You notice a great number of strangely-glowing worms slithering about the feet of the stone trees in Nud-melek.

You notice a great number of strangely-glowing worms slithering about the feet of the stone trees in Nud-melek.\n\nYou should see if the worms' ichor contains any luminescent properties that will be useful to the dwarves of the expedition.
Deep-crawlers can be found in the Second Hall of Nud-melek.\n\nYou should defeat deep-crawlers.
You have collected the valuable glowing ichor of several glow-worms, enough to coat a number of lamps.
Ichor can be found on deep-crawlers in Nud-melek, on the eastern side of the Second Hall.\n\nYou should gather ichor from deep-crawlers.
You have collected the valuable glowing ichor of several glow-worms, enough to coat a number of lamps.
'I recognize that deep-crawler ichor is not exactly the most appealing thing to be gathering. I would suggest you try to keep it from getting on your clothes.'
